# Main.elm — EARLY

TEA bootstrap for the standalone LynRummy Elm game. Wires the
model, Msg, update, view, and subscriptions into
`Browser.element`. Houses the drag/click gesture machinery and
the dispatch loop that applies every validated WireAction
through a single update function.

## Status

- **Label:** EARLY. Active churn — most file edits during the
  autonomy-port work land here. The ambition is that Main.elm
  holds only UI-layer state (drag, popup, replay progress) and
  delegates all game-state transitions to `LynRummy.Game` via
  its extensible-record shape.

## Current scope

Model fields:

- **Game-state fields** (shape of `LynRummy.Game.GameState`):
  `board`, `hands`, `scores`, `activePlayerIndex`, `turnIndex`,
  `deck`, `cardsPlayedThisTurn`, `victorAwarded`,
  `turnStartBoardScore`.
- **UI-layer fields:** `drag : DragState`, `popup`, `status`,
  `hintedCards`, `sessionId`, `score` (running board total),
  `actionLog`, `replay : Maybe ReplayProgress`.

Per the "one log, source-agnostic" invariant: every validated
WireAction — local gesture, replay tick, or (future) wire
receive — flows through `applyWireAction` before anything else
touches the Model. "Capture the input, update the data
structure, re-draw the view."

## Msg and dispatch

- `MouseDown*`, `MouseMove`, `MouseUp` — pointer gesture
  machinery. MouseUp resolves to an optional WireAction and
  runs it through `applyWireAction`.
- `WingEntered` / `WingLeft` — hover state on drop targets.
- `ClickCompleteTurn` — sends CompleteTurn to server (for
  persistence + referee check). On Ok response, the transition
  is committed autonomously via `Game.applyCompleteTurn` using
  client-owned deck. The response's `dealt_cards` is compared
  against the cards the client drew from its own deck as a
  diagnostic (logs to console on divergence) — the server's
  role on CompleteTurn is now "sanity-check me," not "tell me
  what happened."
- `ClickInstantReplay`, `ReplayTick`, `ClickReplayPauseToggle`
  — replay walker controls.
- `ActionSent`, `SessionReceived`, `StateRefreshed`,
  `ActionLogFetched`, `CompleteTurnResponded`, `PopupOk` —
  server round-trip handlers. `StateRefreshed` is the bootstrap
  hydration path on session resume; otherwise state flows from
  applyWireAction alone.

## Subscriptions

- `Browser.Events.onMouseMove` / `onMouseUp` — subscribed only
  while `drag = Dragging _`.
- `Time.every 500 ReplayTick` — subscribed only while
  `replay = Just { paused = False }`.

## View composition

- `viewTopBar` + `viewStatusBar` + flex shell:
  hand column (left, min-width 240px) + board column (right).
- `handColumn` renders the player panel: always P1 above P2,
  active row shows cards + buttons, inactive shows "N cards".
  Single `viewPlayerRow` function called for both seats — the
  view is uniform across every Model-change source.
- `viewPopup` overlays modal ceremony (turn-complete popup).
  Suppressed during replay.

## Replay synthesis (2026-04-21, STILL_EVOLVING)

`buildReplayAnimation` branches on whether a captured gesture
path is present:

- **Faithful branch** — path non-empty → honor it. Plays back
  the captured pointer trace at its recorded pace.
- **Synthesized branch** — path missing → synthesize a linear
  path using LIVE DOM measurement for every viewport coord
  (`stackEdgeInLiveViewport`, `pointInLiveViewport`, and
  the async hand-card DOM query). No pinned-viewport math
  remains in this path. Duration = distance × `dragMsPerPixel`
  (15 placeholder — tuned from 80 for feel).

The distinction is DERIVED at replay time from presence of
data, not tagged at capture time. Matches
`feedback_record_facts_decide_later.md`: record presence,
decide at execution.

### The live board rect (B1 change, 2026-04-21)

When `ClickInstantReplay` fires, Main issues a
`Browser.Dom.getElement boardDomId` task. The result populates
`model.replayBoardRect` (viewport-space x/y of the 800×600
board div). `stackEdgeInLiveViewport` reads this rect to
translate a stack's board-frame `loc` into current viewport
coords — **not** the documentary `BoardGeometry.boardViewport*`
constants. Those constants are now the fallback path (with
a Debug.log warning) for the race where synthesis fires
before the task returns.

### The live hand-card rect (B1-extension, 2026-04-21)

Hand-origin actions (`MergeHand`, `PlaceHand`) need the
drag's starting viewport position. Instead of trusting
`HandLayout.cardCenterInViewport` (pinned math that drifted),
the replay state machine now:

1. In `NotAnimating`, when about to animate a hand-origin
   action with no Faithful path, `prepareReplayStep` issues
   a `Browser.Dom.getElement (HandLayout.handCardDomId card)`
   task paired with `Time.now`. Transitions to
   `AwaitingHandRect`.
2. When `HandCardRectReceived Ok` arrives, the measured
   origin + DOM-measured target combine into an Animating
   animation starting at the piped-through nowMs.
3. On error, Debug.log to dev console and salvage via the
   pinned-math fallback.

Hand cards carry a stable DOM id in `View.viewPlacedHandCard`
built via `HandLayout.handCardDomId`, disambiguated by deck.

**Verified in B1:** live MergeHand replay target lands on the
DOM-measured board rect regardless of what content flows
above the board.

**Verified in B1-extension (2026-04-21, session 24):**
synthesized MergeHand animates from the hand card's actual
rendered position to the board stack's actual rendered edge.
Faithful/Simulated branching works in the same replay — a
human-played move later in the log replays at its captured
pace while Python's earlier merge_hand synthesizes at
15ms/px.

**Still in motion:**
- `MoveStack` synthesis wired via `pointInLiveViewport`
  (synchronous — both endpoints board-frame); not yet
  exercised against a real agent game.
- `Split`, `MergeStack` synthesis not yet wired; they
  apply-immediately-and-beat.

### Rule for adding synthesis to new primitives

**Any viewport coord the replay synthesizer consumes must
come from DOM measurement, not from a pinned constant.** If
you add synthesis for `MoveStack` / `Split` / `MergeStack`:

- For board-frame endpoints, use `stackEdgeInLiveViewport`
  (which reads `model.replayBoardRect`). Do NOT add
  `BoardGeometry.boardViewport*` to a `stack.loc` directly
  anywhere in the synthesis path.
- For anything else that needs a live viewport position of
  a DOM element, follow the MergeHand pattern:
  1. Give the element a stable DOM id.
  2. Fire a `Browser.Dom.getElement` task paired with
     `Time.now`.
  3. Transition to an `AwaitingXRect` intermediate state.
  4. A dedicated `XRectReceived` Msg completes the
     transition into `Animating`, with a Debug.log-only
     fallback on error.

This came from the "landing right, origin wrong" bug
(2026-04-21). The landing was right as soon as the board
rect was DOM-measured; the origin was wrong precisely
because it still trusted pinned math. Every piece of
pinned-viewport math in this path is a latent instance of
the same bug.

## Pointers

- Autonomy-core: `LynRummy.Game` (`Game.elm`) — `GameState`
  record and `applyCompleteTurn` transition. Main embeds those
  fields; changes to game state go through Game's functions.
- Hosted at `index.html` in this dir; built into `elm.js` via
  `npx elm make src/Main.elm --output=elm.js` (runs
  automatically in `ops/start`).
- Served through Gopher at `http://localhost:9000/gopher/lynrummy-elm/`.
- Pinned geometry: `LynRummy.BoardGeometry`,
  `LynRummy.HandLayout`.

